import asyncio
from aiocoap import *
from aiocoap import resource 

class SimpleResource(resource.Resource):
    async def render_get(self, request):
        print(f"Received GET request from: {request.remote}")
        print(f"Payload: {request.payload.decode('utf-8') if request.payload else '(empty payload)'}")
        print(f"Options: {request.opt}")

        payload = b"Hello! This is a GET response from your CoAP server."
        return Message(payload=payload)

    async def render_post(self, request):
        print(f"Received POST payload: {request.payload.decode('utf-8')}")
        return Message(payload=b"POST request received!")

async def main():
    # Create a CoAP server context
    root = resource.Site()
    root.add_resource(('.well-known/core',), resource.WKCResource(root.get_resources_as_linkheader))
    root.add_resource(('',), SimpleResource())  # Resource available at coap://<IP_ADDRESS>/hello

    # Bind the CoAP server to all available interfaces using IPv6 '::'
    await Context.create_server_context(root, bind=("0.0.0.0", 5683))  # Bind to port 5683 on all interfaces

    # Run the server indefinitely
    await asyncio.get_running_loop().create_future()

if __name__ == "__main__":
    asyncio.run(main())
